但是当整个城市都实现了无人驾驶，会发生什么？

192
00:09:48.819 --> 00:09:50.647
Would we need traffic lights?
我们还需要红绿灯吗？

193
00:09:50.671 --> 00:09:52.267
Would we need lanes?
我们需要车道吗？

194
00:09:52.291 --> 00:09:53.790
How about speed limits?
限速呢？

195
00:09:54.383 --> 00:09:56.672
Red blood cells are not flowing in lanes.
血细胞可不是沿着特定的通道移动。

196
00:09:57.222 --> 00:09:59.183
They never stop at red lights.
他们从不在红灯停下。

197
00:09:59.207 --> 00:10:01.183
In the first driverless cities,
第一个无人驾驶城市，

198
00:10:01.207 --> 00:10:03.324
you would have no red lights and no lanes.
不会有红灯和车道。

199
00:10:03.834 --> 00:10:06.907
And when all the cars are driverless and connected,
当车辆都实现无人驾驶并互相联网的时候，

200
00:10:07.450 --> 00:10:11.015
everything is predictable and reaction time, minimum.
任何事情都是可预测的，反应时间达到最短。

201
00:10:10.979 --> 00:10:12.927
They can drive much faster
它们能够驾驶得更快，

202
00:10:12.977 --> 00:10:15.914
and can take any rational initiative that can speed them up
可以理性地做出选择来加速，

203
00:10:15.938 --> 00:10:17.295
